<div class="post"><div class="posttop"><div class="username">Elauriel</div><div class="date">December 11th, 2004, 02:27 PM</div></div><div class="posttext">This stuff happens all the time with moving companies.  They are notoriouus for raising prices after they have your stuff and they will keep and auction the stuff too!  Iit sounds like this company gave you a lowball estimate in order to get your stuff on the truck, then brought out the &quot;real price&quot; which looks a lot more in line with customary moving charges.   I recently paid about $500 JUST for loading and unloading, not for packing, shipping or any assembly/disassembly.  My full-service (pack, ship, store, unpack) move from Mississippi to Chicago in 1997 with only a college student's stuff cost ~4000.  My full-service move from Chicago to North Carolina, with more heavy furniture was $8500.  A recent quote to pack and move me from NC to FL was ~$7000.<br />
<br />
I hope this gets straightened out for you though! Man, I would be freaking.  Never let movers take stuff you can't live without either, like computers or heirlooms (or in my case, my CD's or DVD's).</div></div><hr />


