When my family needed a mover after our folks died and we had to empty the house, we went with a mover that came recomended. Granted, there was an attempt by the driver to scam extra money on delivery but that got squashed fast. All told, I think the bill was for about $2k and that was nearly 5 years ago.<br />
<br />
Moving recently from the Catskills in NY to Erie, PA cost me ~$700 renting a U-haul and loading/unloading myself. The fuel alone probably would've cost you that much using a U-Haul from CA to FL.<br />
<br />
Honestly, $2k is probably in line for the move unless you had next to nothing that they moved. (We didn't have that much either except a piano which is what upped the price and which was the object of scamming on the other end.)<br />
<br />
Anyone who's moved around much have some insights on how to handle this crap? Do moving companies pull this crap when a major company is paying moving expenses too?</div></div><hr />


